<br>
     I'll respond to this.  First, about myself.  I really don't care if it is legalized or not.  I have plenty of friends who do it and my attitude is that I see no problem with it - pot is harmless, I just don''t care about the issue.  <br>
<br>
     That being said, I like to keep the debate intellectually honest.  Everytime I see this we should legalize &quot;Because pot makes great paper and clothes argument&quot; I wince.  Its as if I can smell the big pile of BS that has just been shoveled in front of my face.  People are passionate about legalizing pot because they want to get high.  That's it.  No one gives a one iota about paper, clothes or medicine - they want to get high.  So to those who want to legalize, hold your heads high (bad pun) and say, yes, I want to legalize to get high.  No one is buying the paper industry conspiracy theory.     <p>Norrath: Torcer Arcana - Level 58 Wizard - The Nameless<Br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uverbalsabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Verbalsabre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://verbalsabre.50megs.com/images/lsabre.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/9/02 12:12:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=766.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: who Smokes weed?</span><hr size=1> Well Torcer I would have to respectfully disagree with you. I do agree that the majority of the motivation is that people want to get high but just because that may be their primary concern does not mean that they do not care about the other benefits that would result. <br>
<br>
I for one became a proponent of legalization because I wanted to get high legally but I do strongly believe that legalization would benefit us in many ways. There ARE additional benefits of legalization and we DO believe in them. <br>
<br>
Don't be so synical. Just because they want to get high does not mean they do not care about the enviroment, economy or the medicinal benefits of marijuana. <br>
<br>
There are no facts that can support either one of us in this but I do feel that I am being &quot;Intellectually honest&quot; <br>
